data.value:
Frankfurt, the commercially developed city of Germany; Art museums, galleries, unique historical buildings and fun-filled fair organizations are able to impress their visitors in terms of cultural tourism.
With a population of over 690,000 and surrounded by the River Main, it is possible to see classical-modern buildings intertwined. The Senckenberg Museum, the Frankfurt Cathedral, the St Paul's Church and the Goethe ves House are the historical sights to see. Palmengarten and Frankfurt Zoological Garden attracts nature lovers with its lush texture.
